    relatedCalculators: ["mortgage-affordability", "loan", "savings-goal"],
    content: `<h2>TL;DR</h2><p>Attorney General Merrick Garland’s recent remarks on stablecoin regulation under the GENIUS Act signal potential shifts in the financial landscape that could affect mortgage rates and lending liquidity. For homebuyers, this means it’s more important than ever to lock in affordability now. Use QFINHUB’s <a href='https://www.qfinhub.com/calculators/mortgage-affordability'>mortgage affordability calculator</a> to see how rate changes impact your budget.</p><h2>What Happened</h2><p>On March 11, 2025, Attorney General Merrick Barr delivered brief remarks at The Federalist Society’s event “The GENIUS Act in Practice: Key Questions for Stablecoin Regulation” in Washington, D.C. The speech focused on the regulatory framework for stablecoins—digital currencies pegged to traditional assets like the U.S. dollar. While Barr didn’t announce specific policy changes, his comments underscored the administration’s intent to tighten oversight, which could reduce the use of stablecoins in unregulated lending markets.</p><h2>Why It Matters for Your Mortgage</h2><p>Stablecoins are increasingly used in decentralized finance (DeFi) to provide short-term liquidity for mortgage lenders. Tighter regulation could reduce this liquidity, potentially raising mortgage rates or tightening credit availability. For the average homebuyer, even a 0.25% rate increase can add hundreds to your monthly payment. That’s why now is the time to assess your borrowing power. Use our <a href='https://www.qfinhub.com/calculators/loan'>loan calculator</a> to compare different loan terms and see how rate changes affect total cost.</p><h2>How to Calculate Your Mortgage Affordability</h2><p>To stay ahead of potential rate hikes, follow these steps:</p><ul><li><strong>Step 1:</strong> Estimate your monthly income and debts. A general rule: your mortgage payment should not exceed 28% of your gross monthly income.</li><li><strong>Step 2:</strong> Use the <a href='https://www.qfinhub.com/calculators/mortgage-affordability'>mortgage affordability calculator</a> to input your income, debts, down payment, and interest rate. It will show your maximum home price.</li><li><strong>Step 3:</strong> Run scenarios with a 0.5% higher rate to stress-test your budget. The <a href='https://www.qfinhub.com/calculators/loan'>loan calculator</a> can show you the difference in monthly payments.</li><li><strong>Step 4:</strong> Set a savings goal for a larger down payment to offset higher rates. Use our <a href='https://www.qfinhub.com/calculators/savings-goal'>savings goal calculator</a> to plan how much to save each month.</li></ul><h2>FAQ</h2><h3>What are stablecoins, and why does the government care?</h3><p>Stablecoins are cryptocurrencies designed to maintain a stable value, usually pegged to the U.S. dollar. The government is concerned about consumer protection and financial stability if stablecoin issuers fail to maintain reserves.</p><h3>How could stablecoin regulation affect mortgage rates?</h3><p>If stablecoin liquidity is reduced, lenders may have less access to cheap funding, potentially passing higher costs to borrowers in the form of higher mortgage rates.</p><h3>Should I rush to buy a home now?</h3><p>Not necessarily, but you should be proactive. Use the calculators above to understand your budget under different rate scenarios. If you’re pre-approved, consider locking in a rate sooner rather than later.</p><h3>What’s the best way to prepare for rate changes?</h3><p>Boost your credit score, save for a larger down payment, and use QFINHUB’s <a href='https://www.qfinhub.com/calculators/savings-goal'>savings goal calculator</a> to track your progress. Every percentage point you improve your rate can save thousands over the life of the loan.</p>`,
